So thank you for being here. And thank you to GTC for accepting us here with this talk

6
00:00:48,658 --> 00:00:57,665
about intelligent music. My name is Paltur Paltursson and I work as an audio director

7
00:00:57,665 --> 00:01:05,050
at GCP games, mainly working on EVE Online. In case you don't know what EVE Online is,

8
00:01:05,050 --> 00:01:06,892
it's a sandbox MMO.

9
00:01:08,896 --> 00:01:20,344
with some 20,000 to 60,000 players playing at one time on one server. And with me here

10
00:01:20,344 --> 00:01:30,311
is Dr. Kerstin Oleson, composer and professor who has been working on procedural music for

11
00:01:30,311 --> 00:01:36,796
many years, more than 20 years. And we're going to be talking about something we like

12
00:01:36,796 --> 00:01:37,896
to call intelligent music.

